to: (1) favorable pricing for Majors of $1.9 billion, partially offset by unfavorable pricing for carryover vehicles of $0.5 billion,
inclusive of new revenue standard impacts; (2) increased net wholesale volumes due to an increase in sales of crossover and fleet
vehicles, partially offset by a decrease in sales of passenger cars, planned downtime for full-size trucks and a decrease in sales of
mid-size trucks; and (3) favorable Other due to increased sales of parts and accessories; partially offset by (4) unfavorable mix due
to fleet customer, trim and other mix.
In the year ended December 31, 2017 Total net sales and revenue decreased due primarily to: (1) decreased net wholesale
