Note 21. Earnings Per Share
Basic and diluted earnings (loss) per share are computed by dividing Net income (loss) attributable to common stockholders by
the weighted-average common shares outstanding in the period. Diluted earnings (loss) per share is computed by giving effect to all
potentially dilutive securities that are outstanding.
